CAPE TOWN - Cape Town mayor and former Democratic Alliance Western Cape leader Patricia de Lille is under fire from her party.She and the DA chief whip in the City of Cape Town, Shaun August, have been accused of leaking a confidential party document to the media.The DA says the leak violates the party s policy on the confidentiality of closed meetings.The two are being investigated by the party and there are reports that they could even face suspension.READ: Nothing sinister about resignation, says De LilleDe Lille stepped down from her party leadership role last month, saying she wanted to focus on her role as mayor and devote all her attention to those who voted for her.Her successor will be elected at the weekend.eNCA